        I follow the breathing—it helps a little, which is annoying.

        I say, "Okay, Buddy. Medical supplies. Can you scan for them?"

        Buddy says, "Absolutely! Teamwork makes the dream work! I'm using electromagnetic scanning to detect concentrations of materials consistent with medical equipment! Now, electromagnetic scanning is really interesting—it uses radio waves to—"

        I say, "Buddy. Just tell me where the medical kit is."

        Buddy says, "Right! Safety first! I'm detecting a concentration of medical supplies two point three meters to your left, near the crushed cargo container! Remember to move carefully and watch out for sharp edges!"

        I reach for the supplies, putting weight on my injured leg. Pain shoots up and I nearly fall.

        Buddy says, "Whoa! Remember to move carefully! Maybe we should wait for an adult to help with—"

        I say, "*I AM an adult.*"

        ¶

